    "created_at": "2016-12-05T06:41:43Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-12-05T06:45:00Z",
    "body": "> I'm okay with moving cache folder, but please do not move user settings folder, this isn't worth breaking every app on the planet. Local Storage / Cookies et al are user data for many apps.\r\n\r\n@paulcbetts, I think nobody is suggetting to move user settings... user cache should go to XDG_CACHE_HOME ($HOME/.cache by default)\r\n\r\nIdeally, what you refer to as user data (including databases) should go in XDG_DATA_HOME ($HOME/.local/share by default), chrome doesn't In my opinion correctly do this, but many other Linux apps do.\r\n\r\nUser Settings are already in the correct place (XDG_CONFIG_HOME, defaulting to $HOME/.config).\r\n\r\nIs it possible for Electron to simply add a startup hook (that can be removed in 2.0) that moves the old content, and if necessary, adds a symlink in the old location? And does it solve all the concern from e.g. @baconface?\r\n\r\n\r\n"
  },
