    "created_at": "2016-12-05T09:35:21Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-12-05T09:35:21Z",
    "body": "> Is it possible for Electron to simply add a startup hook (that can be removed in 2.0) that moves the old content, and if necessary, adds a symlink in the old location? And does it solve all the concern from e.g. @baconface?\r\n\r\nThis will be unpredictable and could cause issues with existing applications.  Permission issues, copy speeds and all sorts of other things could cause a working application to suddenly become non-working.  This change should be opt-in not automatic IMO."
