    "created_at": "2017-02-05T01:34:26Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-02-05T01:40:14Z",
    "body": "The same problem exist on macOS and Windows as well. Cache should be stored in `~/Library/Caches/` not `~/Library/Application Support`. Windows as well with `%LOCALAPPDATA%` versus `%APPDATA%`. So not just a Linux problem.\r\n\r\nWhen this is setup correctly then many backup utilities (Time Machine, File History, Dejá Dùp) and indexing agents (Spotlight, ifilter, tracker) will know not to backup or index the contents of these directories. The issue affects device performance and battery life (backing up unnecessary amounts of data over the wifi) as well as platform integration (trash results in on-device searches).\r\n\r\nThe cache folder can be deleted even when electron is running without causing anything but a few cache-misses. Moving it would invalidate the whole cache in one go, but nothing non-recoverable (unless a remote server is offline)."
  },
  {
