    "created_at": "2017-04-22T07:00:34Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-04-22T07:19:07Z",
    "body": "The idea is to define 3 internal variables in Electron for the 3 types of data, by default assigned to the current paths (so nobody is affected by the change), that would be configurable by electron-based apps.\r\n\r\nOnce this change is implemented and the 3 paths become available for configuration to e-app developers, the entire process of migrating existing data of already released e-apps to the new paths, that was debated here, would be shifted to the e-app developers, so each dev team would decide if their app should follow the XDG specification or not. And if they decide to follow it, they could/would assign the default values to the ones mandated by the specification (it would be up to them to make the final decision about the default paths and how to manage the migration).\r\n\r\nSo the idea is not to implement the XDG specification in electron itself, but to make it possible for the e-app developers to *decide* how to manage their data (today they don't have this choice).\r\n\r\nAnd once the e-app devs have this option, the best approach for them would be to make these 3 variables configurable by the user with their default values following the XDG specification."
  },
